        "title": "Undo a cut with the scissor marker",
        "body": "Each cut leaves a scissor marker at its position. Click the marker to undo that cut. When cuts are nested, only the outermost is clickable — remove it first, the next layer becomes clickable on the following render."
      },
      "zoom": {
        "title": "Zoom and snap",
        "body": "Use Zoom out / Zoom in and the slider to scale the timeline. Toggle Snap to make subtitle edges and the playhead lock to nearby block ends and ruler ticks."
      },
      "singleRow": {
        "title": "Keep subtitles in a single row",
        "body": "When subtitles overlap in time, the timeline stacks them into a second row (and beyond). However, the preview only shows the first row, and the rendered video stacks the rest on top of it — so the preview and the final burn-in look different. Adjust your subtitle timings so they fit on a single timeline row without overlap whenever possible."
      }
